285 g Shaved Beef
400 g Mashed potatoes
170 g Green Beans
1 unit(s) Shallot
7 g Chives
28 g Crispy Shallots
2 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
½ tbsp Dijon Mustard
1 g Truffle Sea Salt
1 tbsp Worcestershire Sauce
1 tbsp Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
2 tbsp Milk*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Trim green beans.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add green beans, half the Dijon, half the Worchestershire sauce and 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) water. Cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, until water evaporates and green beans are tender-crisp. Season with pepper and half the truffle salt.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Cook for 30 sec, stirring often, until butter melts.
Remove from heat and transfer to a plate.
Carefully wipe the pan clean.

Meanwhile, peel, then finely chop shallot.
Thinly slice chives.
To a large microwave-safe bowl, add mashed potatoes and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) milk. Season with pepper and remaining truffle salt.
Microwave for 3 min, uncovered, until heated through.
When heated, stir in chives.

Reheat the same pan (from step 1) over high.
Meanwhile, using scissors, snip the side of the beef package and drain.
Cut the beef slices in half.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then shallots. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until shallots begin to soften.
Add beef. Cook for 2 min, flipping occasionally, until beef is cooked through.**
Add broth concentrate, remaining Worchestershire sauce, remaining Dijon and 1/2 cup (1 cup) water. Cook for 2-3 min, flipping to coat, until sauce reduces slightly.

Divide truffle mash and green beans between plates.
Top truffle mash with beef.
Sprinkle crispy shallots over top.